## Usage Tiers

Tiers are based on cumulative spend and account age:

| Tier | Requirements | Automatic upgrade |
|------|-------------|-------------------|
| Free | Default for new accounts | - |
| Tier 1 | $5+ paid | 48 hours after first payment |
| Tier 2 | $50+ paid, 7+ days since first payment | Automatic |
| Tier 3 | $100+ paid, 7+ days since first payment | Automatic |
| Tier 4 | $250+ paid, 14+ days since first payment | Automatic |
| Tier 5 | $1,000+ paid, 30+ days since first payment | Automatic |

## Rate Limit Response Headers

Every API response includes rate limit headers:

```
x-ratelimit-limit-requests: 500
x-ratelimit-limit-tokens: 30000
x-ratelimit-remaining-requests: 499
x-ratelimit-remaining-tokens: 29500
x-ratelimit-reset-requests: 120ms
x-ratelimit-reset-tokens: 1s
```

## HTTP 429 Response

When limits are exceeded:

```json
{
  "error": {
    "message": "Rate limit reached for gpt-4o in organization org-xxx on requests per min (RPM): Limit 500, Used 500, Requested 1. Please try again in 120ms.",
    "type": "tokens",
    "param": null,
    "code": "rate_limit_exceeded"
  }
}
```

## Exponential Backoff with Jitter

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

// The SDK handles retries automatically (default: 2 retries)
const client = new OpenAI({
  maxRetries: 3, // configure max retries
});

// Manual exponential backoff for custom retry logic
async function withBackoff(fn, maxRetries = 5) {
  for (let attempt = 0; attempt <= maxRetries; attempt++) {
    try {
      return await fn();
    } catch (error) {
      if (error instanceof OpenAI.RateLimitError && attempt < maxRetries) {
        const baseDelay = Math.pow(2, attempt) * 1000;
        const jitter = Math.random() * 1000;
        const delay = baseDelay + jitter;
        console.warn(`Rate limited. Retrying in ${Math.round(delay)}ms (attempt ${attempt + 1}/${maxRetries})`);
        await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delay));
      } else {
        throw error;
      }
    }
  }
}

const completion = await withBackoff(() =>
  client.chat.completions.create({
    model: "gpt-4o",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Hello" }],
  })
);
```

## Client-Side Rate Limiting

```javascript
// Simple token bucket rate limiter
class RateLimiter {
  constructor(maxRPM) {
    this.interval = 60000 / maxRPM;
    this.lastRequest = 0;
  }

  async wait() {
    const now = Date.now();
    const elapsed = now - this.lastRequest;
    if (elapsed < this.interval) {
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, this.interval - elapsed));
    }
    this.lastRequest = Date.now();
  }
}

const limiter = new RateLimiter(450); // stay under 500 RPM

for (const prompt of prompts) {
  await limiter.wait();
  const result = await client.chat.completions.create({
    model: "gpt-4o",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: prompt }],
  });
}
```

## Batch API for High Volume

For non-real-time workloads, use the Batch API for 50% cost savings and higher throughput:

```javascript
// Create a batch file
const requests = prompts.map((prompt, i) => ({
  custom_id: `request-${i}`,
  method: "POST",
  url: "/v1/chat/completions",
  body: {
    model: "gpt-4o",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: prompt }],
  },
}));

// Upload and submit batch (completes within 24 hours)
const file = await client.files.create({
  file: new Blob([requests.map(r => JSON.stringify(r)).join("\n")]),
  purpose: "batch",
});

const batch = await client.batches.create({
  input_file_id: file.id,
  endpoint: "/v1/chat/completions",
  completion_window: "24h",
});
```
